               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office prayers and litanies (fols. 3ra-18vb)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 18vb-62vb)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     62vb-177ra)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 62vb-79va)
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ preceded by an excerpt from the “Book of the
                     Testament” (fols. 80va-80va) (cp. MQ, IV, Qǝddāse ʾǝgziʾ, §§1-17) 
 III-3)
                     Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 84va-95va)
 III-4)
                     Anaphora of St John, Son of Thunder (fols. 95va-107rb)
 III-5) Anaphora of
                     the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 107rb-117rb)
 III-6) Anaphora of
                     St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols. 117rb-130rb)
 III-7) Anaphora of St
                     Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols. 130rb-138ra)
 III-8) Anaphora of St John
                     Chrysostom (fols. 138ra-144rb)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Gregory
                     (“Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fols. 144rb-152ra)
 III-10) Anaphora of
                     St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols. 152ra-154vb)
 III-11) Anaphora of St
                     Jacob of Serug (fols. 154vb-161va)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Cyril of
                     Alexandria (fols. 161va-168rb)
 III-13) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea
                     (fols. 168rb-177ra)
 IV) Śǝrʿāta beta krǝstiyān “The Order of the Church”
                     (fols. 177rb-179va). In Amharic
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
